To use this skin:


# Requires
Install each of the below in this order (be sure to wait for each to install before moving on to the next):

01 script.module.unidecode


02 script.module.simpleeval


03 script.skinshortcuts


04 script.globalsearch


05 script.image.resource.select


06 resource.images.weathericons.white


07 resource.images.moviegenreicons.transparent


08 script.skin.helper.colorpicker      


09 script.module.certifi


10 script.module.chardet


11 script.module.idna


12 script.module.urllib3


13 script.module.requests


14 script.module.six


15 script.module.dateutil


16 script.module.typing_extensions


17 script.module.arrow                  


18 script.module.simplecache


19 script.module.routing


20 script.embuary.info


21 script.embuary.helper


22 plugin.video.themoviedb.helper


23 resource.images.studios.white

24 script.module.cherrypy
https://github.com/kodi-community-addons/script.module.cherrypy/archive/master.zip

25 script.module.musicbrainz
https://github.com/kodi-community-addons/script.module.musicbrainz/archive/master.zip

26 script.module.thetvdb
https://github.com/kodi-community-addons/script.module.thetvdb/archive/master.zip

27 script.module.metadatautils
https://github.com/kodi-community-addons/script.module.metadatautils/archive/master.zip

28 script.skin.helper.service
https://github.com/kodi-community-addons/script.skin.helper.service/archive/master.zip

29 script.skin.helper.widgets
https://github.com/kodi-community-addons/script.skin.helper.widgets/archive/master.zip

30 script.skin.helper.skinbackup
https://github.com/kodi-community-addons/script.skin.helper.skinbackup/archive/master.zip

31 script.skin.helper.backgrounds
https://github.com/kodi-community-addons/script.skin.helper.backgrounds/archive/master.zip

32 script.tv.show.next.aired
https://github.com/kodi-community-addons/script.tv.show.next.aired/archive/master.zip

Once the above are installed, then download the Aura skin from my repository (new version that has requirements for the above is live), it will take time to install, please wait until completed.

Once installed, you can switch to Aura skin and try it out.

-----------------------------

RottenTomatoes and Metacritic Setup via SkinHelper and OMDB api

1. Install the beta version of skin helper from marcelveldt's beta repository (and update all relevant dependencies e.g. metadatautils , skin helper and simplecache).
https://github.com/kodi-community-addons/repository.marcelveldt/raw/master/repository.marcelveldt-1.0.3.zip



2. Go to omdb and get an API key. If you are lucky you can get a free key, but please consider donating to omdb via Patreon to keep omdb alive
http://www.omdbapi.com/apikey.aspx

3. Once you have an API key, go to Skin Settings > Manage Dependencies and click "script.module.metadatautils" to open it's settings

4. Go to the API section of the settings and enter your omdb api key, then press OK to save your settings.

5. Close Kodi and delete simplecache.db from kodi/userdata/addon_data/script.module.simplecache/simplecache.db - this step is not necessary, but it will force skin helper to rebuild its info cache and retrieve the ratings.

6. Open kodi and your ratings should now work. It can take a little while for skin helper to retrieve ratings for the focused item the first time around, so make sure you give it a little bit of time before reporting problems.

7. SkinHelper is heavily rate limited if you do not also have api keys for TMDb and Fanart.tv - I recommend also getting api keys for these.


------------------


Still many fine details to work out, but in general it is useable.

